java.awt

Class PopupMenu.AccessibleAWTPopupMenu

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.accessibility.AccessibleContext
      • java.awt.MenuComponent.AccessibleAWTMenuComponent
        • java.awt.MenuItem.AccessibleAWTMenuItem
          • java.awt.Menu.AccessibleAWTMenu
            • java.awt.PopupMenu.AccessibleAWTPopupMenu
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AccessibleAction, AccessibleComponent, AccessibleSelection, AccessibleValue
    Enclosing class:
    PopupMenu

    protected class PopupMenu.AccessibleAWTPopupMenu
extends Menu.AccessibleAWTMenu
    Inner class of PopupMenu used to provide default support for accessibility. This class is not meant to be used directly by application developers, but is instead meant only to be subclassed by menu component developers.

    The class used to obtain the accessible role for this object.

    Since:
    1.3
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
